{"id": "duc04-testb-23:12#37", "contents": "Cardoso's efforts to reduce the deficit are part of a deal with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) for a $30 billion rescue package. The plan aims to restore investor confidence in Brazil's economy, which has been battered by the global financial turmoil. The government has agreed to annual targets to sharply reduce the deficit through 2001. However, many Brazilians are skeptical about the effectiveness of these measures, pointing out that other areas of government spending remain unchecked. The leftist Workers Party has criticized the government for focusing on minor savings while ignoring more significant expenditures."}
